{
  "stem": "7832.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Children were crying constantly, constantly crying to go home, to go home, when we going to go home?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was holding my sister.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She-- [CRYING] she was begging me for water, and I couldn't give her any water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CRYING] And the parents were trying to console us and promise that it'll be better, it'll be better, tomorrow will be better, but tomorrow was so long away.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was like it never was going to come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so after a while, we were in that train for so long and it was so horrible that we didn't care where we went, as long as they'd just open the door so we could just breathe some air or see some light.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and the-- the train did stop.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They did open the door.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[CRYING] And then we didn't see much light.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[CRYING] When they opened the doors, they didn't let us off right away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They said only the-- the women and the children should come off the train, and the boys and the men should stay behind.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So of course, being gentlemen, they let the women and the children go first.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when we got off the-- the wagon, they just marched us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother was holding my-- my little brother in her arms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the other arm, she held my sister's hand.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was holding my sister's hand, so we walked together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My two brothers were-- stayed back with my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were walking and then we-- and-- and these people in black uniforms [CRYING] with rifles yelling, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we moved into this one direction, and then there was this one man with a baton, like a magic wand in his hand.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was flipping that thing back and forth, telling people where to go.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
